<br>
After about an hour of soloing, hardly budging my xp bar, I see a wizard running by with 4 toilers on his tail.  They are all snared and he is AoE’n them like mad.  I was like WTH?  I thought he was in trouble till I watched in awe as he killed them all with ease.  I thought nothing of it, and continued to solo to my hearts conent.<br>
<br>
Then, about 10 minutes later, he was back with 4 more.  AoEing them with no problems at all, and sucking up xp like its going out of fashion.  I was like, something is wrong here.  Here I am pulling one mob every 6 minutes, having a pet beat on it, and taking less than half the xp, while this guy is pulling 4 mobs every 10 and taking full xp for them all?  Does anyone else see the fairness in this situation?  Why must pet classes get the nerf for soloing when this guy over here is pulling 4, and getting full xp for them all?  For every 10 mobs I pull he is pulling 20 with no xp penalty?<br>
<br>
Verant, please please remove the solo xp penalty for us pet classes.  The pet is a buff or ability that we mages possess, and we should not be nerfed for something that YOU gave us.  How do you see the logic in having the pet take more XP if he does more damage?  If a warrior and a cleric is grouped up together, and the cleric does nothing but heal the warrior, does the warrior get more XP for doing more damage?  I think not, as that would be downright unfair, as the cleric is giving health to the warrior, in essence giving the warrior the ability to do more damage.  I think the same should be said for us pet classes.  If I want to play the cleric role with my pet, and I just heal the pet while he beats on the mob, should I get less XP for doing this?  I think not, as I am keeping the pet alive just like a cleric would do.  I don’t see the logic behind this penalty.<br>
<br>
Now, you might say that since the cleric and warrior are grouped up, that they would both get the same XP, half each if they are both the same level, granted race/class XP penalties and such.  If us mages cannot get all of the XP from our solo battles, then at least give the pet half the xp, and us half.  And if that is the case, give our pet abilities to learn small skills within soloing, maybe to raise the dmg a little during the fight, just like a warrior would do in the low levels.<br>
<br>
The best move would be to not give pets XP, as it doesn’t benefit the pet in any way.  Our pet is a spell, a buff, a DoT, a DD, however you look at it, that cost mana to upkeep it and keep it going.  Mages live by their pets, we have no utility spells (ex. Root, slow, snare, etc.)  I think I speak for many mages when I post this.  Thank you for your time and ear in this matter.<br>
<br>
Eldain<br>
59 Magician<br>
