<br>
To put it more simply...<br>
<br>
Pet &lt; Melee of the caster's level.<br>
<br>
A pet can tank pitifully compared to a Melee, it has not the armor class, though it only has decent hit points. It's role is to damage stuff, abusively. To penalize a class for using it's primary mode of offense is Just Plain Stupid.<br>
<br>
Besides, the reason it wasn't lifted was because of this misguided concept of &quot;Risk vs Reward&quot;. Sorry, but what he really means is &quot;Power vs Vulnerability&quot;. In a magician/pet pair is Pet is the power, providing the magician ample time to cast without being beat on. The penalty is NO defense what so ever if the pet falls. No stun, no root, no snare, no evac, no succor, no mez, no charm, no rune, nothing.<br>
<br>
Risk vs Reward is I fight a real nasty mob, I win, I get rewarded my proper reward.<br>
<br>
Power vs Vulnerability is My pet is strong, but without him, I am defenseless.<br>
<br>
